definition.value: A 3-hydroxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the 3-carboxy group of (3S)-3-carboxy-3-hydroxypropanoic acid.
A glycosylglycerol that is glycerol in which the hydroxy groups at positions 1 and 2 have been converted into the corresponding L-fucopyranoside and D-glucopyranoside derivatives, respectively.
An acyl-CoA having citramalyl as the S-acyl group.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of an alpha-L-fucopyranose residue and a D-galactopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
